item.title: FAST ELA Florida Reading Test Bootcamp – Help Your 3rd Grader Get Promoted to 4th Grade!
item.dc:creator: tutors-login@yopmail.com
item.content:encoded:
Is Your 3rd Grader at Risk of Retention Because He/She is Struggling with Reading? This is Their LAST CHANCE to Pass the FAST ELA Reading Test & Move to 4th Grade! Overview: If your third grader is struggling with reading and comprehension, this intensive 20-session, 20-hour bootcamp is designed EXCLUSIVELY to help them master key literacy skills and pass the FAST ELA Test—a requirement for promotion to 4th grade. Avoid the pain of possible retention in 3rd grade - your child may be closer to promotion than you know!

What Your Child Will Gain:

  • Expert Tutoring – Small group (6:1 or less) instruction from certified teachers
  • 20 Hours of Focused Reading & Comprehension Prep – Build fluency, vocabulary, and critical thinking skills
  • Test-Taking Strategies – Proven techniques to answer comprehension questions with confidence
  • All Materials Included – Practice passages, reading exercises, and targeted skill-building activities
  • Guaranteed Readiness – Your child will walk into the test prepared and walk out with a passing score!

Course Objective:

To effectively prepare 10th-grade students for the Florida Assessment of Student Thinking (FAST) English Language Arts (ELA) test, it's essential to focus on the Benchmarks for Excellent Student Thinking (B.E.S.T.) standards that are most heavily assessed. According to the FAST ELA Test Design Summary and Blueprint, the distribution of content areas and their respective weightings for 10th grade are as follows:
  • Reading Prose and Poetry: 25–35%
  • Reading Informational Text: 25–35%
  • Reading Across Genres & Vocabulary: 35–50%

Based on these weightings, the following 20-day, 20-hour pacing guide emphasizes the standards with the highest value to help 10th graders perform well on the FAST ELA test.

Is Your High School Student at Risk of Not Graduating? This is Their LAST CHANCE to Pass the FAST ELA Test & Meet the Graduation Requirement!

Parents - If your 10th/11th/12th grader is struggling with reading comprehension, writing, and vocabulary skills, this intensive 20-session, 20-hour bootcamp is designed EXCLUSIVELY to help them master key literacy skills and pass the FAST ELA Test—a requirement for high school graduation. Avoid summer school and graduation issues with personalized support that your child will actually absorb.

What Your Child Will Gain:

  • Expert Tutoring – Small group (6:1 or less) instruction from certified teachers
  • 20 Hours of Focused Reading & Writing Prep – Build analytical reading, essay writing, and test-taking confidence
  • Test-Taking Strategies – Learn proven techniques to maximize scores on multiple-choice and essay sections - these skills are as important as reading ability
  • All Materials Included – Practice tests, reading exercises, and step-by-step writing support
  • Guaranteed Readiness – Your child will walk into the test prepared and walk out with a passing score!

Course Objective:

To effectively prepare 10th-grade students for the Florida Assessment of Student Thinking (FAST) English Language Arts (ELA) test, it's essential to focus on the Benchmarks for Excellent Student Thinking (B.E.S.T.) standards that are most heavily assessed. According to the FAST ELA Test Design Summary and Blueprint, the distribution of content areas and their respective weightings for 10th grade are as follows:
  • Reading Prose and Poetry: 25–35%
  • Reading Informational Text: 25–35%
  • Reading Across Genres & Vocabulary: 35–50%

Based on these weightings, the following 20-day, 20-hour pacing guide emphasizes the standards with the highest value to help 10th graders perform well on the FAST ELA test.
